The paper discusses the challenges of detecting and reconstructing the timeline of events in cloud computing, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a novel architecture for detecting and correcting time alterations in compromised hosts and guests, which involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE) concepts. The paper also mentions the use of simulation to evaluate the proposed framework, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
